The paper deals with argumentation-based dialogue systems and their optimization using deep reinforcement learning. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of deep reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information retrieval and seeking, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
